## Association Types

### belongs_to (One-to-One, Many-to-One)

Model has a foreign key pointing to another model.

```ruby
# app/models/article.rb
class Article < ApplicationRecord
  belongs_to :user
  # Requires user_id column in articles table
  # Article belongs to one User
end

# app/models/user.rb
class User < ApplicationRecord
  has_many :articles
  # User has many Articles
end
```

**Usage:**
```ruby
article = Article.first
article.user           # Returns associated User
article.user_id        # Returns user ID

user = User.first
user.articles          # Returns array of Articles
user.articles.count    # Count articles
```

**belongs_to Options:**
```ruby
class Article < ApplicationRecord
  # Optional association (user_id can be NULL)
  belongs_to :user, optional: true
  
  # Custom foreign key
  belongs_to :author, class_name: 'User', foreign_key: 'author_id'
  
  # Counter cache (adds articles_count to users table)
  belongs_to :user, counter_cache: true
  
  # Touch parent updated_at when this changes
  belongs_to :user, touch: true
  
  # With validation
  belongs_to :category, optional: false  # Requires category
end
```

