### has_one (One-to-One)

Model has one associated record.

```ruby
# app/models/user.rb
class User < ApplicationRecord
  has_one :profile
  # User has one Profile
  # Profile has user_id foreign key
end

# app/models/profile.rb
class Profile < ApplicationRecord
  belongs_to :user
end
```

**Usage:**
```ruby
user = User.first
user.profile              # Returns Profile or nil
user.profile.create(...)  # Create profile for user
user.profile = profile    # Assign profile to user
```

**has_one Options:**
```ruby
class User < ApplicationRecord
  # Dependent destroy
  has_one :profile, dependent: :destroy
  
  # Required (must have profile)
  has_one :profile, required: true
  
  # Custom class/foreign key
  has_one :account_settings, class_name: 'Profile', foreign_key: 'user_id'
end
```

