### has_and_belongs_to_many (Many-to-Many, Simple)

Direct many-to-many without join model.

```ruby
# app/models/article.rb
class Article < ApplicationRecord
  has_and_belongs_to_many :tags
end

# app/models/tag.rb
class Tag < ApplicationRecord
  has_and_belongs_to_many :articles
end
```

**Database Structure:**
```ruby
# articles table
- id
- title

# tags table
- id
- name

# articles_tags table (no id, no timestamps)
- article_id
- tag_id
```

**When to Use:**
- Simple many-to-many relationship
- No additional attributes on join table
- No need to track when association was created

**Prefer has_many :through when:**
- Join table needs timestamps
- Join table needs additional attributes
- More flexibility needed

